INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0604735F$$, 2027, $$COMBAT TRAINING RANGES (CTR): Portfolio provides electronic warfare equipment and support to Air Force combat training ranges for training, testing, and
evaluation of aircrews. Development and integration efforts include aircraft pods, radar emitters, advanced training radars, communication jammers, command and
control and debrief capability, and instrumentation equipment. The portfolio will also research and develop analytical and information management, data management,
digital environments, networks, facilities, and security infrastructure. All development efforts support USAF aircraft for Joint, Coalition, and Live Virtual Constructive
(LVC) training events.

ADVANCED RADAR THREAT SYSTEM Variant 3 (ARTS- V3):
ARTS-V3 is developing the most advanced ground-based radars in the US inventory using digital active electronically scanned radar technology used to simulate the
latest foreign peer adversary Surface-to-Air Missile (SAM) radar and Electronic Warfare (EW) threat systems. ARTS-V3 systems are a critical part of the Operational
Training and Test Infrastructure (OTTI) plan for developing future Tactics, Techniques and Procedures (TTPs) for 5th/6th generation aircraft (F-35, B-21, F-47). ARTS-
V3 systems are critical for Department of the Air Force test capabilities for validation of advanced airpower capabilities against threat-representative radar systems and
validation of models used for the Joint Simulation Environment (JSE).

ARTS Technology Development:
Address the affordability training gap with government-owned, software-defined mobile emitters that increase threat density and realism of an integrated air defense
network. Efforts include developing a technical data package, building prototypes, maturing production capabilities, and transitioning items for production.

LIVE MISSION OPERATIONS CAPABILITY (LMOC): LMOC is a government-owned command system serving as the training range equivalent of an Air Operations
Center (AOC). Connecting all CAF ranges through a secure, dedicated network backbone, LMOC utilizes a long-term, modular, and scalable architecture to enable real-
time mission planning, execution, and debriefing. This multi-domain, multi-security level environment facilitates the integration of 4th/5th/6th generation live-synthetic
training by supporting blue/red/white force cells from pre-event preparations through live monitoring to post-event debriefing and data storage. LMOC features provisions
for future Live, Virtual, and Constructive (LVC)/Blended and Joint interoperability test and training requirements enhancing warfighter capabilities.

 P6 Combat Training Systems (P6CTS) will resolve existing critical training capability gaps and will enable comprehensive, realistic air combat training. Key upgrades
 include a trusted operating system, Multiple Independent Levels of Security (MILS) architecture, Type 1 encryption of over-air data, and increased processing capability.
 P6CTS investment will support a robust Air-to-Air and Air-to-Ground combat training environment and provide a growth path to Blended Training capability. The P6CTS
 is comprised of airborne participant subsystem, ground system/subsystem and ancillary range communication infrastructure. P6CTS Initial Operating Capability (IOC) on
 F-15 at Nevada Test and Training Range (NTTR) is targeted for FY28.

