Title: Advanced Radar Threat System Tech Development                                                                             7.737      2.336       2.637      0.000        2.637
Description: The ARTS Tech Development Program refines the designs, develops technical data packages,
builds prototype systems, and matures systems for production. Efforts include but are not limited to research,
studies, technology data package development, software development, engineering, and manufacturing
medium-cost radar emitters.

FY 2026 Plans:
In FY2026, the program office is initiating a rapid prototyping contract to build test articles for an affordable threat
emitter design concept that has the potential to fulfill a set of current shortfalls in live-emitter training needs
for the F-35 aircraft and other aircraft platforms at regional training ranges. Success of this effort will inform
divestment decisions for aging legacy range emitters that are well beyond service life and facing significant
sustainment obsolescence challenges and rising repair costs.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
In FY2027, the program office is continuing a rapid prototyping contract to build test articles for an affordable
threat emitter design concept that has the potential to fulfill a set of current shortfalls in live-emitter training needs
for the F-35 aircraft and other aircraft platforms at regional training ranges. Success of this effort will inform
divestment decisions for aging legacy range emitters that are well beyond service life and facing significant
sustainment obsolescence challenges and rising repair costs.
FY 2027 OOC Plans:
N/A
