LMOC utilizes the agile software acquisition pathway and will continue iterative development to transition the
LMOC Platform to a higher classification level capability that meets training and test requirements of USAF 4th
and 5th Gen combat systems and communities. This includes the use of fully automated proficiency-based
training augmentations for debrief and data analysis at each combat system's wartime classification level which
will dramatically increase the speed that combat units can gain combat proficiency and test units can adjudicate
system capabilities prior to release to the CAF.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
LMOC is continuing to utilize the agile software acquisition pathway and will continue iterative development to
transition the LMOC Platform to a higher classification level capability by further developing and accrediting the
Prism solution for Special Access Required programs, thereby meeting training and test requirements of USAF
4th and 5th Gen combat systems and communities.
FY 2027 OOC Plans:
N/A
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY2027 decrease due to results in software development delays required to meet Air Combat Command
security architecture and multi-level security requirements.
Title: P6 Combat Training System (P6CTS)                                                                                18.524      15.211      11.472      0.000       11.472
Description: P6CTS will replace the existing P5CTS and the Misawa/Osan/Kunsan/Kadena Instrumentation
Training System (MOKKITS). P6CTS will resolve existing critical training capability gaps and will enable
comprehensive, realistic air combat training. Key upgrades include a trusted operating system, Multiple
Independent Levels of Security (MILS) architecture, Type 1 encryption of over-air data, and increased
processing capability. P6CTS investment will support a robust Air-to-Air and Air-to-Ground combat training
environment and provide a growth path to Blended Training capability.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continued funding of Non-Recurring Engineering (NRE) to complete F-15/F-16 and range integration at Nevada
Test and Training Range (NTTR) in support of P6 Initial Operating Capability (IOC) and continued development
of Air Battlespace Shaping (OABS). FY26 deliverables include the F-15 Affinity Profile Image and ACE software

