Title: Advanced Radar Threat System-Variant 3 (ARTS-V3)                                                                  117.791 111.062    112.208   0.000 112.208
Description: ARTS-V3 program has designed the US's most advanced ground-based radars. The program
continues to develop, build, and test the advanced Surface-to-Air Missile (SAM) radar threat systems. ARTS-V3
will replicate strategic/tactical threats at the fidelity necessary for 5th and 6th generation multi-domain platform
engagements. The ARTS-V3 requirement is to develop a modular radar threat system that has a rapid software
development and integration capability to replicate multiple advanced SAM threats and support Live Virtual
Constructive (LVC) training. Efforts include but are not limited to development of Production Representative
Articles (PRA) and prototypes, development of command-and-control software, developmental/operational
test, digital engineering, pre-production activities, and efforts focused on integrating ARTS-V3 into live virtual
constructive architectures and test and training ranges.

FY 2026 Plans:
The focus of FY2026 is building the Production Representative Article (PRA) and conducting combined
developmental/operation test activities. Activities will include but are not limited to remaining hardware
purchases, fabrication of radar sub-assemblies and higher level assemblies, component-level and sub-system
level testing, continued development of the command & control software, integration activities with the command
& control software, software-defined threat profile development/integration, and engineering activities to reduce
integration risk during open-air full system testing in FY2027.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
FY2027 focuses on completing manufacture, integration, test, and delivery of the ARTS-V3 X-band in FY2027
and C-band in FY2028 in order to enable production start in FY2028. Integration efforts will focus on open air
testing and achieving IOC at the Nevada Test and Training Range.
FY 2027 OOC Plans:
N/A
