Description: The program utilizes RDT&E funds to develop and deliver space vehicles (SVs) 11-12, conduct the Non-recurring
Engineering (NRE) of developing risk-reducing simulators (Global Positioning System (GPS) Software and Simulator (GSS+ 1
& 2), (GPS Non-flight Satellite Test Bed (GNST+)), developing support test equipment, and conducting the systems engineering
associated with delivering the new capabilities required of GPS III Follow On (GPS IIIF) including backward compatibility, dual
band Telemetry, Tracking, and Control, integration of Government Furnished Equipment hosted payloads, and Regional Military
Protection (RMP), which delivers high power regional Military-Code (M-Code) signals in specific areas of intended effect. In
conjunction with the delivery schedule, the GSS+ require an extended period of performance for implementation and operations.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue Development of GPS IIIF SV 11 and SV12. Continue development and initiate launch vehicle assembly of GPS IIIF
SV12. Continue the build, qualification, and delivery of GSS+ which will be utilized for Mission Readiness testing, Integrated
Cyber Testing, System Integration Demo 31, and Space Vehicle risk reduction events and provide critical capabilities for on-orbit
checkout testing (OOCT) and anomaly resolution for the GPS IIIF constellation. As part of overall GPS IIIF advanced capabilities
development, continue developing the Enhanced Command & Control/Modular Open System Approach capability through
Implementation Design Review 1 (IDR.1)/Preliminary Design Review, continue development toward a GPS IIIF optical crosslinks
demonstration (as a follow-on to the GPS III SV10 crosslinks demonstration), continue the On-Orbit Reprogramming capability
through IDR.1. GPS IIIF crosslinks IDR will focus on risks, interoperability to the larger architecture, and incorporating/validating
commercial/driving modernization of capabilities. GPS IIIF will continue special studies targeted to mitigate on-ramp capability
risks.
Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
