Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction,
prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond
to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 Funding decreased due to the delivery of risk-reducing simulators (GSS+) and reduction in costs in late-stage
development of SVs 11 and 12.
Title: Resilient GPS                                                                                                                         -       15.000          0.000
Description: Will conduct trade studies and analysis towards furthering efforts completed with Phase 0 of Resilient GPS. Effort
focused on proving out new, flexible architectures and will implement lessons learned from Phase 0.

FY 2026 Plans:
Certify on-orbit, reprogrammable cryptography unit(s) to meet SERD 2.0 requirements, capitalize on new commercial capabilities,
and mitigate major schedule risk. Validate program anti-jam opportunity, which could deliver key anti-jam capability to the
warfighter using MGUE Inc 1. Design and prove out new, flexible architectures for GPS monitoring stations and data transport to
take advantage of industry advancements and prepare control segment for a proliferated constellation
