Description: The PNT Architecture effort leverages lessons learned from Resilient GPS phase 0 to modernize the space
and ground supply chain by integrating commercial solutions, enabling the rapid delivery of mission-critical capabilities to the
warfighter in response to emerging threats. Program will conduct trade studies and analysis towards developing an integrated
PNT Architecture.

FY 2026 Plans:
Initiate contracts for studies and analyses that will inform the development of a next-generation, reprogrammable, adaptable, and
cost-effective future PNT enterprise architecture. Assess the application of Modular Open Systems Approaches (MOSA) and the
integration of commercial capabilities and technologies on a wide range of architectural alternatives and development pathways
for both space and ground segments.
Program activities will include analysis, trade studies, modeling (MBSE), simulation, and prototyping to evaluate the feasibility,
benefits, and risks of various architectural constructs for both space and ground.
