FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue market research activities for the acquisition of subsystems
- Conduct fiber optic/network design reviews and factory acceptance tests
- Conduct system performance analyses with latest ionospheric data
- Conduct ionospheric and electromagnetic interference data collections in the receive site (Angaur, Palau)
- Continue Model Based System Engineering (MBSE) activities
- Start Cybersecurity and Risk Management Framework process for fiber optic cable subsystem
- Select system integrator
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will initiate contract execution activities
- Will conduct System Level Design Reviews to enter production
- Will start purchase of long lead items
- Will start sensor management software suite design, development, and update activities
- Will continue buildout and deployment of on-island fiber optic/WAC network segments
- Will continue ionospheric modeling to inform target tracking software development activities
- Will conduct electromagnetic interference surveys at the transmit site (Babeldaob, Palau)
- Will fund program support costs to include DCA manpower, test assets, and initiation of iterative integrated developmental and
operational testing
