A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Efforts funded in this program focus on development, testing, and fielding, of a long-range early detection capability for airborne and surface targets of interest. Each
line of effort acquires and fields a land based, high-frequency (HF) ionospheric, backscatter Over-the-Horizon RADAR (OTHR) for detection and tracking of airborne and
surface targets over wide geographic areas. Fielding of this capability will enable detection, tracking and reporting of airborne and surface targets that may be obscured
from conventional line of sight radar systems by the curvature of the earth. Specific lines of effort funded include, but are not limited to, Tactical Multi-Mission Over the
Horizon Radar (TACMOR), Homeland Defense Over-the-Horizon Radar (HLD OTHR) and support for a classified United States European Command (USEUCOM)
requirement.

 TACMOR is a US Air Force remotely operated OTHR system being developed for deployment in the Republic of Palau (RoP). The system will provide enhanced Air
 Domain Awareness in key regions of USINDOPACOM's area of responsibility. TACMOR FY 2026 funds were allocated to - Program 012417F Project 674865 (budget
 authority 7). FY 2027-FY 2031 corrects the budget authority from 7 to 5 to appropriately reflect program efforts.

 HLD OTHR efforts are focused on the development of a capability to provide long range early warning for North America in response to emerging threats. The
 program's intent is to design, develop, test and field advanced OTHR systems operating at levels of sensitivity far exceeding current US OTHR systems in operation.
 Program activities include transmit subsystem development and integration, command and control (C2) interface design and integration, HF sensor and digital receiver
 technology advancement, ionospheric characterization research, remote sensor management capability development, and sensor data fusion research. HLD OTHR data
 will be distributed and integrated into existing Integrated Air and Missile Defense (IAMD) early warning networks, to include the emerging architectures as applicable.

 In support of the Air and Cruise Missile Defense of the Homeland (ACMD-H) mission and North American Aerospace Defense Command (NORAD)/United States
 Northern Command USNORTHCOM (N/NC) Defense of North America mission, the project focuses investments to enhance capability for OTHRs.

 HLD OTHR will continue executing experimental efforts with the Department of War science and technology community to characterize ionospheric conditions in
 Continental United States (CONUS) locations.

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program
 funds would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in PE 0605827F, 0605828F, 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605832F, 0605833F, 0605898F, 0606398F. In FY
 2025, 3.65 million was expended for civilian pay expenses in this program element, and in FY 2026, 0.11 million is forecasted for civilian pay expenses in this program
 element.


