A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Homeland Defense (HLD) Over-the-Horizon radar (OTHR) efforts are focused on the development of a capability to provide long range early, warning for North America
in response to threats. The program's intent is to design, develop, test and field advanced OTHR systems operating at levels of sensitivity far exceeding current US
OTHR systems in operation. Program activities include command and control (C2) interface design and integration, transmit sub-system development and integration,
HF sensor and digital receiver technology advancement, ionospheric characterization research, remote sensor management capability development, and sensor data
fusion research. HLD OTHR data will be distributed and integrated into existing Integrated Air and Missile Defense (IAMD) early warning networks, to include the
emerging architectures as applicable.

 In support of the Air and Cruise Missile Defense of the Homeland (ACMD-H) mission and North American Aerospace Defense Command (NORAD)/United States
 Northern Command USNORTHCOM (N/NC) Defense of North America mission, the project focuses investments to enhance capability for OTHRs.

 HLD OTHR will continue executing experimental efforts and procure necessary upgraded hardware with the Department of War science and technology community,
 including federally funded research and development center, defense laboratories, and small business expertise to characterize ionospheric conditions in CONUS
 locations.

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds
 would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in PE 0605827F, 0605828F, 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605832F, 0605833F, 0605898F, 0606398F. In FY 2025,
 3.865 million was expended for civilian pay expenses in this program element.

 HLD OTHR development is not a new start. The program received initial funding in FY 2023 under the North Warning Systems Program (0102412F). The DAF realigned
 the funding in FY 2024 to Over-the-Horizon Backscatter Radar Program (0102417F) to report all DAF OTHR efforts.

 The HLD OTHR program utilized FY 2025 28.0 million for a Rapid Acquisition Authority requirement.

 The total cost of the HLD OTHR Middle Tier of Acquisition (MTA) effort is 1.103 billion, including research, development, test, and evaluation (RDT&E) and procurement
 funding for prototype units.

 This program is in Budget Activity 5, System Development and Demonstration (SDD) because it has passed Milestone B approval and is conducting engineering and
 manufacturing development tasks aimed at meeting validated requirements prior to full rate production.


