D. Acquisition Strategy
TACMOR plans to enter the Middle Tier of Acquisition pathway, as a Rapid Prototyping effort(MTA-RP). The program leverages the Air Force Tactical Exploitation of
National Capabilities (TENCAP) and Joint Capability Technology Demonstration (JCTD) system designs to mature final production prototype design. Development,
integration, testing, and fielding activities will be executed via a system integration contract award. Contracting strategy maximizes the use of established government
contracts, e.g., General Services Administration (GSA) schedules, Indefinite Delivery/Indefinite Quantity (IDIQ) contract vehicles, consortia agreements.




