Note
In FY2024 and FY2025 Cognitive Electromagnetic Warfare executed within PE 0604270F, Electronic Warfare Development, Project 653891, Adv Infrared Counter
Measures (AIRCM). In FY2026 the Cog EW efforts were transferred to PE 0207039F, Cognitive Electronic Warfare, Project 650099, Cognitive Electronic Warfare.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This program integrates multiple projects to achieve massed non-kinetic warfare dominance for the Department of War (DoW) Counter Long Range Kill Chain (C-LRKC)
and Counter-Command, Control, Communications, Computers, Cyber, Intelligence, Surveillance, & Reconnaissance (C-C5ISR) constructs. It includes three initial
interrelated activities that capture and exploit EW effectiveness improvements/synergies in contested/congested battlespaces. These activities include: 1) Algorithm and
Applications (Algo & Apps) 2) EW Dev Env and 3) MEAP.

 The Alg & Apps project continues efforts initiated under PE 64270F in FY2024 (as Cog EW) and extends those actions to identify/discover, investigate, and nominate
 potential advanced algorithms that can fill gaps in our abilities to automatically sense the electromagnetic environment, employ machine learning (ML) to understand
 it, and adapt or create new electromagnetic countermeasures in real-time to defeat adversary capabilities. This provides agile and adaptive responses to novel,
 ambiguous, and complex adversary radar and communication systems.

 The EW Dev Env project ties together several on-going AF, other service, and commercial activities by building and utilizing an evolving digital infrastructure to advance
 promising algorithms through an integrated disciplined maturation/validation process constituting the front end of an ""EW Application Pipeline” as the entry point of an
 AF standard methodology for producing and delivering advanced capabilities to rapidly meet operational requirements and transition advanced technologies to fielded
 capabilities in collaboration with weapon system program offices and ACC's 350th Spectrum Warfare Wing (SWW). It leverages work done under AFRL's E-Gon and
 the AF Open Architecture Test Pipeline (AOATP) efforts. This process will ultimately be used to implement Cog EW attributes into fieldable and supportable warfighting
 capabilities.

 The Mod EA Payloads (MEAP) project is a use case exemplar exercising the Algo & Apps and EW Dev Env processes to produce fieldable supportable advanced EA
 capabilities for applications in multiple crewed and uncrewed platforms. It will produce various form factor payloads for integration into Open Architecture hardware/
 software platforms providing both offensive and defensive EA for host and other airborne entities in contested/congested environments.




