Title: EMBM Development                                                                                                                 0.000      17.693        45.322
Description: Perform assessments and analyses of government off the shelf (GOTS) systems and applications capability
to analyze friendly, neutral, and adversary use of the electromagnetic spectrum (EMS). Received data will be displayed in a
common operation picture to enable situational awareness, planning, and decision making. Assisted by machine learning/artificial
intelligence EMBM will share EA techniques, system identification and targeting criteria across the Joint warfighting force to
perform effective Non-Kinetic Fires in a contested Electromagnetic Operational Environment (EMOE).

FY 2026 Plans:
DAF Electromagnetic Battle Management program will execute a second weapons control test demo and start work under the
System Development Contract. Contract work will focus on software integration, SA tool and system architecture back bone
development efforts to set the metrics required to document Early Operational Capability (EOC). Data collected will influence
the system-to-system integration work and AI/Machine Language efforts to reach the goal of EOC by the FY28Q1. Concurrently
the EMBM IT Infrastructure thrust will begin development of the modern architecture required for the program to link into the DAF

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025       FY 2026      FY 2027
Battle Network. The program will also fund the building of and ramp-up of an EW System Program Office to be in place for Initial
Operating Capability and LRIP sprint efforts post EOC.
FY 2027 Plans:
DAF Electromagnetic Battle Management program with continued efforts towards delivering an Early Operational Capability (EOC)
system by 1QFY28. To do so, the best of breed Government-off-the-Shelf systems delivering Situational Awareness, Command
and Control (C2) and Decision Support data, along with displaying a common operating picture will undergo system-of-system
integration. The resulting prototype will then undergo live-fly demonstrations to test compatibility and deliver test metrics and
validate the on-going platform integration efforts showcasing C2 capability to airborne units. Development on the Training suite
will start and run parallel with the other integration work. EMBM IT Finally, the Electromagnetic Warfare System Program Office
will be activated and readied for initial Low-Rate Initial Production efforts.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding increased to account for multiple live-fly demonstrations and the start-up of platform integration efforts with subject demo
aircraft to reach EOC by 1QFY28.
