Note
In FY2024 and FY2025 the Electromagnetic Battle Management (EMBM) program executed within PE 060427F, Electronic Warfare Development, Project 653891, Adv
Infrared Counter Measures (AIRCM).

In FY2026 the EMBM efforts were transferred to PE 0207407F, Electromagnetic Battle Management, Project 650098, EMBM.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Department of the Air Force (DAF) Electromagnetic Battle Management (EMBM) program is an automated family of systems/applications linked by common
architectures, standards and data that will expeditiously receive, analyze, display, employ, and securely distribute friendly, neutral, and adversary Electromagnetic
Spectrum (EMS) information. DAF EMBM will consist of five component capabilities; the ability to attain, maintain, and monitor the spectrum for EMS Situational
Awareness (SA), assessment, and mission planning, decision support with command and control, and training interfaces to all levels of EMS Operations (EMSO). The
coordination and synchronization of EMSO will provide real-time Non-Kinetic Fires Orchestration across domains in any range of military operations. DAF EMBM will
feed into USSTRATCOM's EMBM-Joint (EMBM-J) at the Combatant Command-level enabling synchronization of Joint Non-Kinetic Fires and enabling resilient decision
advantage in contested EM environments.

This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program
funds would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program element 00605827F, 0605828F, 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605832F, 0605833F, 0605898F,
0606398F.

This program is in Budget Activity 5, System Development and Demonstration (SDD) because it has passed Milestone B approval and is conducting engineering and
manufacturing development tasks aimed at meeting validated requirements prior to full rate production.




