Operational Systems Development$$, $$AFIPPS is being acquired as a Defense Business System that utilizes the Business Capability Acquisition Cycle. The program is in Phase 4 - Acquisition, Testing, and
Deployment and was working towards its first Limited Deployment Authority to Proceed (ATP) for a Limited Deployment in 2026.

 The acquisition strategy employs a single System Integrator and agile methodologies to develop, test and deploy pay and leave capabilities via an Oracle Enterprise
 Resource Planning (ERP) E-Business Suite (EBS). The primary system integrator contract includes pay system development, test, and deployment. The development
 activities were fully coordinated and integrated with the on-going operation and sustainment of the Military Personnel Data System (MilPDS).

 Due to system performance risks associated with a single-release of pay and leave to all Department of the Air Force (DAF) military members, the DAF restructured
 the program to execute Limited Deployments prior to a Full Deployment to all DAF military members. In third quarter fiscal year 2025, the Milestone Decision Authority
 (MDA) directed 90-day pause to allow the DAF to revalidate functional requirements. The 90-day strategic pause delayed the program's first Limited Deployment and
 refocused efforts on military pay requirements.

 The plan was for the DAF to conduct OT&E prior to each deployment. The OT&E strategy implemented a two-phased approach. Phase 1 comprised Operational
 Assessment or Operation Utility Evaluation testing to determine operational effectiveness and suitability prior to the Limited Deployment Authority to Proceed (ATP)
 decisions. Phase 2 comprised an Initial Operational Test and Evaluation (IOT&E) event to further validate system efficacy and readiness to support pay/leave for all
 remaining DAF members. Upon completion of IOT&E and a successful Full Deployment Authority to Proceed (ATP) decision, the AFIPPS pay/leave capability would be
 released to all Airmen and Guardians.

 After successfully completing all test initiatives, Full Deployment and a year-long sustainment with Air Force Operational Test and Evaluation Center (AFOTEC) led post
 deployment analysis, the DAF was going to transition AFIPPS to the Capability Support Phase.

 The contracting activities will focus on completing termination efforts.

