Description: Automated Test and ReTest (ATRT) Enterprise Rapid Capability develops, integrates, and
deploys novel capabilities aggregated from mature technologies in support of Distributed Maritime Operations.
These capabilities are enabled through the use of virtualized systems of systems, automated test and analysis,
automated certification, rapid interface development, and field with and data collection and edge analytics..
These technologies are at the heart of the Navy's rapid capability approach, which combines digital engineering
tools with evolutionary approaches to requirements generation, operational testing, and deployment. This
process will meet Fleet demands for near-term capability in a predictable and repeatable fashion.

Project 9B88 Automated Test and Analysis is an effort shared between the NAVSEA PE 0603598N and
NAVWAR PE 0603597N. This effort is an increase to continue NAVSEA efforts previously funded by NAVWAR.
Funding is required to test and analysis for Hard/Soft Kill as well as Long Range Fires capability improvements.

FY 2025 Plans:
N/A
FY 2026 Base Plans:

                                                                                  APID DEVELOPMENT

