 manufacturing development tasks aimed at meeting validated requirements prior to full rate production.$$, $$The Weapon Storage and Security System (WS3) is a US maintained/operated system of systems that supports the nuclear mission by providing the capability to
securely and safely store resources deployed in Europe. The Vault Modernization Program (VMP) ensures National Security Directive 42 (NSD-42) compliance and
addresses system obsolescence issues. Detailed information is classified and can be provided.

 Funding is required for VMP to deliver an NSD-42 compliant encryption system necessary to secure forward deployed nuclear weapons in Europe in time to meet the
 required need date. A non-compliance will result in the need for US and NATO partner nations to post unplanned and unfunded security forces continuously until a
 compliant encryption system is delivered and installed. Detailed information is classified and can be provided.

 This program is in Budget Activity 5, System Development and Demonstration (SDD) because it has passed Milestone B approval and is conducting engineering and
 manufacturing development tasks aimed at meeting validated requirements prior to full rate production.

