FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE: The KC-46A is evaluated against traditional Research and Development (R&D) program expenditure benchmarks. Unlike many traditional R&D
programs, the KC-46A EMD contract is a Fixed Price Incentive Fee (FPIF) contract with progress payments. Twenty percent (20%) of incurred costs are withheld until the end
of the contract, when they are liquidated. Mandatory funding obligations and progress payment withholds will cause the program to lag traditional expenditure benchmarks,
painting an inaccurate portrait of overall program health.

